Arsenal have announced a new kit deal with German sportswear giant Adidas.
The Gunners will don Adidas strips from the beginning of the 2019/20 season after their five-year deal with Puma expires at the end of the current campaign.
A statement on the club’s Twitter feed said: “Arsenal and Adidas have agreed a new kit partnership, effective from July 1, 2019.
